(80, 'NUEVA', 'DOCUMENTAL \"ACORTADO\"', 183, 13, 'AKILIMALI MAGE Alfred', NULL, 'Certification\'s coordinator', NULL, 'alfredakilimali@yahoo.fr', NULL, '+243990776553', NULL, 'Joachim MUNGANGA MAHEMU', NULL, 'joachimmunganga@yahoo.fr', NULL, '+243994742998', NULL, '8866', '8866', '17826029,50 Kg Of Charries', '< 15 ha; except Eugene Muhima (24 ha) and Kalume Bahavu (25 ha) Sector Minova,  Maheshe Kazige (45 ha) in Sector Nyamassasa and Alver Kayanik (52,1 ha), Muhima Eugene (Plantation Kea) (32,25 ha) and Amana Sagara (182 ha) in Tsheya Sector', 'The SOPACDI cooperative has 16 sectors: TSHEYA, BUTUMBA, KILUKU, BWEREMANA, BISHANGE, KALUNGU, NYAMASASA, RUHUNDE, BWISHA, MINOVA, KIHUMBA, KISHENYI, BUNYAKIRI, BUGARULA, KANENGE, KINIEZIRE. We have Three(3) washing stations. With 27 field oficers, and 57 Saisonal works.de ', NULL, NULL, '8865 members in 16 OPP ', '16 sectors', 'The products are:\r\n1. Coffee charries,\r\n2. Coffee Parchemnt\r\n3. Green Coffee Beans.', NULL, 1, 1, 1, 'We are subcontracted with JAMBO SAFARI in coffee processing.', NULL, 'SOPACDI has 97 collection centers with 3 washing stations(Tsheya, Nyamasasa and Idjwi) and 1 subcontracted prossessing ', 'Producers are monitored on a daily basis by the field officers  at a rate of 325 producers per instructor who, with the forms \"Fumo ya Ukaguzi ya ndani and Fumo ya Kiingilio cha shamba\", completes them at least twice a year. And this is done exclusively to the members of the cooperative, that is to say those with a written contract.\r\nThe SCI documents of each producer are kept in the agronomists\' offices of the sectors and others in the office of the coordinator. These documents consist of a copy of a written contract between the planter and the cooperative, the identification form (Fumo ya Kiingilio) and the control sheet (Fumo ya Ukaguzi ya ndani) and others listed above and The office of the coordinator there is the computer that has all the data and the daily cards of purchase cherry.\r\nThe sanctions are taken by the SCI coordinator after receiving the report of the monitors, the testimonies of his neighbors and the filling of the card attesting to the fault of the producer. The fault considered heavy is only the use of chemicals in the coffee field or use of seeds GMO (seeds not controlled by the cooperative and whose source is not known). The remnants of the faults are considered to be mild, and only advice is given to the planter.\r\nThe misuse of chemicals in the field of coffee is considered as a gross fault and the planter is suspended in the cooperative for a period of 3 years and all this period its production will not be bought by the cooperative.\r\nTraining is provided at different levels. We have routine training that is provided daily by the instructors during the passage of a monitor in the field of the farmer and also at least once a month in the demonstration fields or we regroup the planters in contact group (GC) constituted by 20 - 30 planters.\r\nWe also have large training sessions in the meeting rooms or we train the trainers who in turn will provide training on the ground.\r\nThe training themes are varied according to the need felt on the ground (from the production to the transformation of the coffee through the agroforestry and the protection of the ecosystem).\r\nThe unconventional cultivation practiced is tomato which is also produced only by a non-member minority of the cooperative. SCI asks these members not to grow the tomato and if its non-member peasant neighbor cultivates it, it is necessary to leave a distance between the infected area and the biological area a minimum distance of 3 meters if it uses chemical fertilizers , 5 meters if sprayed, 2 meters if growing GMOs or planting a natural wall there are herbs.\r\nConsidering that in our environment the last time of chemical use in the fields dates from the colonial era, the conversion period is 12 months. But if it is proved that in the field there was use of the chemicals as fertilizer, the plantation is organic only after 3 years of conversion and attested by the monitors after a careful follow-up or two visits every year', 'There was some minor non compliances such as: \r\nFor the organic, some fields were not registred in the grows list: Fullfiled \r\nFor the Flo, some works paid the taxe others no; Fullfiled ....', 'NO', NULL, '3/11/2016', NULL, 'AKILIMALI MAGE Alfred', NULL, '../../archivos/ocArchivos/cotizaciones/1487235333_Offer_SOPACDI_DRC_20161103.pdf', NULL, 1485348827, 1488566935, 8, 12),
